On the island of Wakoku, the civil war offers anyone the chance of becoming a hero &mdash; from fishing women to bastard children, any can make a name for themselves by working through the rigorous ranks of the army. Hinowa, a young woman with extraordinary skills, is determined to do just that, but soon learns things may not always go to plan&hellip; More than ten years after a disastrous battle, the war is still ongoing, and a girl with black hair and black markings washes up on shore&hellip;
